18/12/2003
NEW YORK, United States -- Iraqi Foreign Minister Hoshyar Zebari met with Bulgarian counterpart Solomon Passy Wednesday (17 December) on the sidelines of a UN Security Council meeting.
Zebari expressed gratitude for Bulgaria's role in the stabilisation of Iraq, in Sofia's capacity as a president of the Council this month.
Passy was in New York to preside over the Council's open meeting on Kosovo.
He welcomed UNMIK chief Harri Holkeri's initiative to establish more concrete guidelines for implementation of the "standards before status" policy.
(Trud, 24 Chassa - 18/12/03;
BTA, BNT, bTV - 17/12/03)
